In this example we demonstrate structural change detection in the context of oil
prices' relationship with the U.S. Dollar. Commodities in general are priced in
dollars, and thus their prices tend to have an inverse relationship with the
overall strength of the dollar relative to other currencies; as the dollar
strengthens, commodity prices tend to fall. We see that pattern in oil prices as
well. In Figure \ref{fig:oildollar} we observe the inverse relationship between
dollar strength and oil price. Additionally, we observe that at least one of the
series (specifically, oil prices) appears to be heteroskedastic, with volatility
appearing to increase after the 1990s.

